        whyItMatters: 'If Isaiah 1 is safely historical, it cannot confront the modern reader. But if it is addressed to the religiously active \u2014 to people who look like us \u2014 then every verse becomes a mirror. The chapter\'s power depends on the reader recognizing themselves in the defendants, not observing them from the gallery.',
