        ntRef: 'Amos 5:21-24',
        connection: 'Amos, Isaiah\'s contemporary, delivers a nearly identical prophetic rejection of worship without justice: "I hate, I despise your festivals... But let justice roll down like waters, and righteousness like an ever-flowing stream." The parallel confirms that this is not Isaiah\'s personal complaint but a consistent divine message across multiple prophets. God\'s rejection of performative worship is a theme, not an aberration.',
